data.text: @trollprincess Yeah, that was *intense*. I immediately wanted to see it again when it was over, but I'm also not sure I ever want to see it again.

@akachaneen As stunned as I was by the ending of Infinity War, that moment in the car in Hereditary ... I just ... I literally stared at the screen with my jaw dropped open for five straight minutes. And then the *wailing*. Damn.
@trollprincess Oh wow, that's fantastic! Especially Toni Collette, since horror movies get shafted so often by any non-genre awards. She was incredible.
Also, Toni Collette got nominated for Hereditary and Michael B. Jordan got nominated for Black Panther so I'm happy to see two of my favorite performances of the year on the list.
I mean, in a perfect world you could pull off gender neutral nominations and not see them lean male all the time, but this is good.
